.TH IX.IO "1" "December 2025" "ix.io 202208111053-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ix.io \- Command-line pastebin client for ix.io service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ix.io
[\fI\,FILE|TEXT\fR...] [\fI\,OPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B ix.io
.I COMMAND
[\fI\,ARGUMENTS\fR] [\fI\,OPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B cat FILE
|
.B ix.io
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ix.io
is a command-line pastebin client for posting text, code, and files to the ix.io pastebin service via HTTP API. It provides a simple interface for creating, updating, and managing pastes with support for authenticated users, automatic URL clipboard copying, and multiple input methods (files, stdin, direct text).
.PP
The script simplifies pastebin operations by providing command-line pastebin posting (files, text, pipes), authenticated user account support (persistent credentials), paste management (create, update, delete, retrieve), automatic URL clipboard copying, desktop notification integration, and saved URL history tracking.
.PP
ix.io is particularly useful for quick code/log sharing via command line, automated script output posting to pastebin, terminal-based paste management without browser access, integration with clipboard managers for URL copying, and persistent pastebin history tracking.
.PP
.B Note:
The ix.io service appears to have shut down (line 650 in script shows "It appears ix.io has shutdown"). This tool is preserved for historical reference and as a template for pastebin clients.
