.SH PASTE MANAGEMENT
How ix.io manages existing pastes:
.SS Deleting Pastes
.RS
.EX
ix.io -d ABC123
# or
ix.io -d http://ix.io/ABC123

# Success: Deleted paste ID: ABC123
# Failure: Failed to delete paste ID: ABC123
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Requires authentication (user must own paste)
.IP \(bu 2
Uses HTTP DELETE method
.IP \(bu 2
Extracts paste ID from URL or direct ID
.IP \(bu 2
Response: "deleted" or "couldn't delete"
.RE
.SS Updating Pastes
.RS
.EX
ix.io -i ABC123 newfile.txt
# Output: Updating paste ID: ABC123
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Requires authentication (user must own paste)
.IP \(bu 2
Uses HTTP PUT method instead of POST
.IP \(bu 2
Replaces existing paste content
.IP \(bu 2
Response: "couldn't replace" on failure
.RE
.SS Retrieving Pastes
.RS
.EX
# Get paste with metadata (plus format)
ix.io id ABC123

# Get raw paste content
ix.io raw ABC123
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
.B id
command: Appends + to URL (metadata format)
.IP \(bu 2
.B raw
command: Direct URL access (raw content)
.IP \(bu 2
No authentication required for retrieval
.IP \(bu 2
Output sent to stdout
.RE
.SS Auto-Nuke (Self-Destruct)
.RS
.EX
ix.io -n 5 file.txt
# Output: Setting autonuke to 5 reads
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Paste auto-deletes after N reads
.IP \(bu 2
Uses -F read:1=N form parameter
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for temporary shares
.IP \(bu 2
Cannot be undone after posting
.RE
.SH CURL INTEGRATION
How ix.io uses curl for HTTP operations:
.SS HTTP POST (Create)
.RS
.EX
curl -X POST -F f:1=@"filename" http://ix.io
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
-F f:1=@FILE: Multipart form upload
.IP \(bu 2
Returns paste URL on success
.IP \(bu 2
-4: Force IPv4 (avoid IPv6 issues)
.IP \(bu 2
-LSsf: Follow redirects, silent, fail on HTTP errors
.RE
.SS HTTP PUT (Update)
.RS
.EX
curl -X PUT -F f:1=@"filename" http://ix.io/ABC123
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
Same as POST but with PUT method
.IP \(bu 2
Requires paste ID in URL
.IP \(bu 2
Returns updated paste URL
.IP \(bu 2
Authentication via --user flag
.RE
.SS HTTP DELETE (Remove)
.RS
.EX
curl -X DELETE --user "user:pass" http://ix.io/ABC123
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
DELETE method removes paste
.IP \(bu 2
Requires authentication
.IP \(bu 2
--max-time 3: 3 second timeout
.IP \(bu 2
Returns "deleted" or "couldn't delete"
.RE
.SS Authentication Method
.RS
.EX
curl --user "$IX_IO_USER_NAME:$IX_IO_USER_PASS" --basic
.EE
.IP \(bu 2
HTTP Basic Authentication
.IP \(bu 2
Credentials from config file
.IP \(bu 2
--basic: Force Basic Auth method
.IP \(bu 2
Sent with all authenticated requests
.RE
